summary: An automated email notification from the DOJ's E2 travel system reminding a traveler that a voucher for a trip to West Palm Beach for victim interviews in the U.S. v. Epstein case is late. The trip was for July 11-12, 2019, related to case number 2018R01618.

events.title: Travel for Epstein Victim Interviews
events.description: A DOJ traveler took a trip to West Palm Beach for the purpose of conducting victim interviews for the U.S. v. Epstein case.

keyFacts: The document is a late voucher notification for a DOJ trip related to the U.S. v. Epstein case (2018R01618).
The trip's purpose was 'Victim Interviews' for the case, indicating ongoing investigative activity in July 2019.
The travel occurred on July 11-12, 2019, to West Palm Beach, Florida.
The document originates from the DOJ's internal E2 travel system, showing official government travel for the case.
The case is referenced as 'R19NYS13654 - U.S. v. Epstein (2018R01618)'.
